Both the multiple reaction monitoring experiments and analyses of the total features detectable in the  retention time contour plots suggest that a very large number of peptides are present in - runs of total proteome digests (16, 17). e recently investigated the dynamic range of single -/ runs and found that even very low-abundance proteins could be detected in this mode (18). urthermore, direct analysis without prefractionation implies high sensitivity because only a few micrograms of peptides are required to load the column to capacity. owever, our previous study was performed with a dedicated chromatographic setup and would not be straightforward to adopt for nonspecialized groups.Both the multiple reaction monitoring experiments and analyses of the total features detectable in the MS retention time contour plots suggest that a very large number of peptides are present in LC-MS runs of total proteome digests (16, 17). We recently investigated the dynamic range of single LC-MS/MS runs and found that even very low-abundance proteins could be detected in this mode (18). Furthermore, direct analysis without prefractionation implies high sensitivity because only a few micrograms of peptides are required to load the column to capacity. However, our previous study was performed with a dedicated chromatographic setup and would not be straightforward to adopt for nonspecialized groups.
