A novel mass spectrometer, the  xactive, couples a mass selective quadrupole to the rbitrap analyzer (19). n this bench top instrument, precursor ions are selected by the quadrupole, fragmented by higher energy collisional dissociation (20), and measured at high resolution and mass accuracy in the rbitrap analyzer. ycle times for a top10 method (survey scan followed by up to 10 / scans) are β�1 s, more than twice as fast as with previous instruments of the rbitrap family. hus the  xactive offers the potential to analyze many more peptides in a given time, with very high / data quality. e wanted to combine these benefits with ultra  (),1 which was not available to us in the previous single-run analyses. aking advantage of a newly developed compact  system termed the -n. LC 1000, we achieved higher chromatographic performance with relatively long columns and small particle diameters. Here, we describe this simple but powerful bench top platform and evaluate its capability to characterize the yeast proteome in high throughput but also in-depth fashion.
